## Objective
Set up an Ubuntu Desktop virtual machine in VMware.

## Tools Used
- VMware Workstation
- Ubuntu Desktop ISO

## Steps Performed
1. Created Ubuntu VM in VMware
2. Assigned 4GB RAM, 2 CPU cores, and 50GB storage
3. Installed Ubuntu Desktop
4. Ran system updates
5. Installed open-vm-tools
6. Created a clean snapshot

## Outcome
- Successfully deployed Ubuntu VM
- Verified internet access
- Confirmed VMware integration features worked

## Key Concepts Learned
- Linux VM creation
- Package updates with apt
- Snapshot management
